				<sawd:HTML fmt="html" captionID="kcap12832459_1948">&lt;font color=darkblue&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Description :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Oracle BIEE can leverage value-based hierarchies to aggregate metric information in distinct ways; either using a rollup aggregation at each level or using an individual contribution for each level.
The three reports in this example show three distinct examples of hierarchy based aggregations. Flat aggregation only shows the metric value for each individual contribution (records in the fact table that have this individual value key). Rollup aggregations cumulate the individual value plus all the cumulated sum of it&#39;s descendants values. The distance based aggregation indicates the value for each individual broken down by &#39;generation distance&#39; to the individual.</sawd:HTML>
			</sawd:htmlView>
			<sawd:htmlView name="HTML 3" duid="0oaouic28aft8dk3">
